<item>
            <title>[CXF-3096] Closing JMS endpoint always destroys SingleConnectionFactory</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-3096</link>
                <project id="12310511" key="CXF">CXF</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;On calling close() on a JMSConduit or  calling shutdown() on a JMSDestination the used SingleConnectionFactory gets always destroyed.&lt;br/&gt;
This must not be done in any cases because the same SingleConnectionFactory might be used by other JMS endpoints (e.g. if configured in using the JMSConfig-Feature).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This should be fixed in a way that the JMSConfig should record if it automatically has created the SingleConnectionFactory(e.g. JNDI use-case), only in this case it should be destroyed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also see: &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-2788&quot; title=&quot;Bus.shutdown() did not close all the created Jms connection&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CXF-2788&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CXF-2788&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
